    Is Elon Musk Trying to Make Humans Useless?
  </header>

  <div class="container">
    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/ed/Elon_Musk_Royal_Society_%28crop2%29.jpg" alt="Elon Musk">

    <h2>The Rise of AI and Automation</h2>
    <p>
      Elon Musk, the billionaire entrepreneur behind Tesla, SpaceX, and Neuralink, has long been at the forefront of technological innovation. But with his push for artificial intelligence, robotics, and brain-computer interfaces, some people have begun to wonder: is he making humans useless?
    </p>

    <h2>From Self-Driving Cars to Robot Workers</h2>
    <p>
      Tesla's self-driving technology aims to eliminate the need for human drivers. At the same time, companies like Tesla are investing in robots that can perform repetitive labor-intensive tasks. As these machines grow smarter and more capable, they may start replacing human workers in various industries.
    </p>

    <h2>Neuralink: A Human-AI Symbiosis</h2>
    <p>
      Musk claims that the purpose of Neuralink is to help humans stay relevant in an age of AI by enhancing our brains with technology. But this raises a questionâ€”will everyone have access to such enhancements, or will it create a new divide between the upgraded and the rest?
    </p>

    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>
      While Musk says his goal is to help humanity, the rapid advancement of his technologies might end up sidelining a large part of the human population. It's not necessarily about making humans useless, but rather about shifting what it means to be useful in a high-tech future.
    </p>
